- The integer array parameter `nums1` and `nums2` must have the same length `n`.
- All values in the integer array parameters `nums1` and `nums2` are greater than or equal to 0 and are less than or equal to 10^7.
- The integer result is the minimized XOR sum after rearranging the elements of `nums2`.
- The XOR sum is calculated as `(nums1[0] XOR nums2[0]) + (nums1[1] XOR nums2[1]) + ... + (nums1[n - 1] XOR nums2[n - 1])`.
- The XOR operation is a bitwise operation that results in 1 if the bits are different and 0 if the bits are the same.